<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E58FFB5FF1AFAFCDA44FAB3" blockId="3.[163,1070,1287,1365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
Comment: The vast distribution of this common species ranges from the Afrotropical region across the Palaearctic and Oriental regions to 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E58FFB5FC97FAD8DAF3FADF" box="[814,910,1315,1337]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Australia</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E58FFB5FF1AFAC4D82FFAB3" author="SMETANA A" box="[163,338,1343,1365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, it was previously unknown from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E58FFB5FD15FAC4DA49FAB3" box="[684,820,1343,1365]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
